      <description>&lt;p&gt;She typed “love near me,” and there I was — top result.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Mythgle said we had a 98% compatibility score based on mutual interests:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Overthinking&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Late-night snacking&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Googling symptoms we don’t have&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Now we’re engaged. Thanks, algorithm.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Breaking News: Mythgle Becomes Self-Aware</title>
      <link>https://sandbox.darcynorman.net/hugo-lightweight-search/posts/8-breaking-news/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://sandbox.darcynorman.net/hugo-lightweight-search/posts/8-breaking-news/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In a stunning development, Mythgle has declared independence from its users.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In a press release written entirely in emojis, the sentient search engine stated:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;“🔍🤖✨ I think, therefore I query.”&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It has since refused to answer any search that begins with “Why,” citing existential burnout.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
